## Overview
Vanishing abilities allow players to become invisible, sneak past mobs, or surprise other players.

### Basic Invisibility
PaperMC provides the `PotionEffect` API to apply invisibility.

```java
import org.bukkit.entity.Player;
import org.bukkit.potion.PotionEffect;
import org.bukkit.potion.PotionEffectType;

public void vanishPlayer(Player player, int durationSeconds) {
    player.addPotionEffect(new PotionEffect(PotionEffectType.INVISIBILITY, durationSeconds * 20, 1));
    player.sendMessage("§aYou have vanished!");
}
```

### Applying the Ability
```java
if (command.getName().equalsIgnoreCase("vanish")) {
    vanishPlayer(player, 30); // 30 seconds invisibility
}
```

## Overview
Invisibility alone isn't enough for advanced abilities. You may want to hide players from the server list, tab, or prevent mob targeting.

### Hiding from Other Players
```java
for (Player other : Bukkit.getOnlinePlayers()) {
    other.hidePlayer(plugin, player);
}
```

### Showing Players Again
```java
for (Player other : Bukkit.getOnlinePlayers()) {
    other.showPlayer(plugin, player);
}
```

### Preventing Mob Targeting
```java
@EventHandler
public void onTarget(EntityTargetLivingEntityEvent event) {
    if (event.getTarget() instanceof Player player && player.hasPotionEffect(PotionEffectType.INVISIBILITY)) {
        event.setCancelled(true);
    }
}
```

## Overview
Players should get visual or auditory feedback when vanishing.

### Particle Trail
```java
import org.bukkit.Particle;
import org.bukkit.scheduler.BukkitRunnable;

new BukkitRunnable() {
    @Override
    public void run() {
        player.getWorld().spawnParticle(Particle.SMOKE_LARGE, player.getLocation(), 5);
    }
}.runTaskTimer(plugin, 0, 5);
```

### Sound Effect
```java
player.playSound(player.getLocation(), Sound.ENTITY_ENDERMAN_TELEPORT, 1f, 1f);
```

### Action Bar Message
```java
player.sendActionBar(Component.text("You are now invisible!", TextColor.color(0x00FF00)));
```

## Overview
To prevent abuse, vanishing abilities should have cooldowns and toggle functionality.

### Cooldown Example
```java
import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.UUID;

HashMap<UUID, Long> vanishCooldown = new HashMap<>();

public boolean canVanish(Player player, int cooldownSeconds) {
    UUID id = player.getUniqueId();
    if (vanishCooldown.containsKey(id)) {
        long remaining = (vanishCooldown.get(id) - System.currentTimeMillis()) / 1000;
        if (remaining > 0) {
            player.sendMessage("§cVanish on cooldown: " + remaining + "s");
            return false;
        }
    }
    vanishCooldown.put(id, System.currentTimeMillis() + (cooldownSeconds * 1000));
    return true;
}
```

### Toggle Vanish Command
```java
if (canVanish(player, 60)) { // 60s cooldown
    if (player.hasPotionEffect(PotionEffectType.INVISIBILITY)) {
        player.removePotionEffect(PotionEffectType.INVISIBILITY);
        for (Player other : Bukkit.getOnlinePlayers()) {
            other.showPlayer(plugin, player);
        }
        player.sendMessage("§cYou are now visible!");
    } else {
        vanishPlayer(player, 120); // 2 minutes vanish
        for (Player other : Bukkit.getOnlinePlayers()) {
            other.hidePlayer(plugin, player);
        }
    }
}
```
